Food Allergy
,
Intolerances
, details of preferences,
Geolocation Data
, we will be able to provide with you a better and personalized service.
If you provide us with personal information about other people (e.g. family members or colleagues) during your hotel reservation or stay, we ask you to ensure that they are willing to share their personal information with us and to direct them to this Privacy Policy if they would like to know how we use their information.
In addition: We automatically collect your information when you use our website, mobile applications, interact with our other digital channels and, in some cases, when we communicate with you by email. In these cases, information such as your country information, Internet protocol ("IP") addresses, intermediate access control addresses, your interactions with these channels, and other characteristics about your system or device may be automatically collected. This information is collected to complete the functionality and improve the experience of using the services. This information is also used to aggregate trends and statistical analysis to show you more relevant ads and information.
Sensitive personal information
Certain types of personal information described in this Privacy Policy are considered "sensitive" information and subject to other applicable rules depending on the jurisdiction and applicable laws in which you work or reside. Where applicable, the personal information referred to in this Privacy Policy shall be deemed to include sensitive personal information, if any.
"Sensitive Personal Information" as defined by Chinese laws and regulations that we collect and use for the purposes set forth in the Privacy Policy above include the following information:
Food allergy
Accommodation records;
Location information;
Payment card information (used to pay for hotel stays, deposits or other services);
Children's information
We take the protection of children's personal information very seriously. Our website and services are mainly aimed at adults. Children should not create their own user accounts without parental or guardian consent. Although local laws and customs define children differently, we consider anyone under the age of 14 to be a child.
In the case of the collection of child user information with the consent of parents or guardians, we will only store, use or publicly disclose this information if it is permitted by law, with the express consent of parents or guardians or necessary for the protection of children, otherwise we will seek to delete the relevant data as soon as possible.
Due to the limitations of existing technology and business model, it is difficult for us to proactively identify children's personal information. If you find that we have collected children's personal information without our knowledge or without prior consent of verifiable guardians, you may contact us in time and we will try to delete it in a timely manner upon discovery. If we ourselves find any of the foregoing circumstances, we will also remove them in a timely manner, except for those required to be retained by law.
The exception to authorized consent
Please understand that according to laws and regulations and relevant national standards, we do not need to obtain your authorization and consent to collect and use your user information under the following circumstances:
1. Directly related to national security and national defense security;
2. Directly related to public security, public health and major public interests;
3. Directly related to criminal investigation, prosecution, trial and execution of judgment;
4. In order to protect your or other individuals' life, property and other major legal rights and interests, but it is difficult to get the consent of the person;
5. Your user information collected is disclosed to the public by yourself;
6. Your user information collected from legally disclosed information, such as legal news reports, government information disclosure and other channels;
7. Necessary to sign or perform the contract according to your requirements;
8. Necessary for the safe and stable operation of the software and related services, such as discovering and handling faults of the software and related services;
9. The person who controls the personal information shall be the news organization and necessary for it to carry out lawful news reports;
10. When an academic research institution conducts statistics or academic research in the public interest and provides the results of academic research or description to the public, it de-identifies the personal information contained in the results.
11. Other circumstances stipulated by laws and regulations.
How do we use the information we collect
Unless otherwise stated to you at the time of data collection, or otherwise authorized by law or by you, we use personal Information only for the purposes described in this Privacy Policy. We use the personal information collected by MHI also for the following purposes:
Operate, maintain, upgrade and provide all the featured services, provide you with required services and information, respond to comments and questions, and provide support for users.
Understand and analyze user trends and preferences, improve MHI hotel services, and develop new products, services, features and functions. We (with your consent or as permitted by applicable law) may, based on your preference, send you commercial information through E-mail and/or traditional letters and/or SMS and/or telephone and etc. to share products, services, promotions, specials, events or other related matters with you. If you do not want to receive these promotional messages, you can opt out of receiving these promotional messages via
privacy@melia.com
or via the withdrawal option provided in each of the commercial communications received.
Share and disclose your personal information with third parties
We may share and disclose your personal information with third parties as explained in the "To which Recipients will the User's Data be Disclosed" section of the Privacy Policy.
In case you request to benefit from the services offered by MeliáRewards program partners (including airlines, shopping, car renting, leisure and others), we will communicate your data to such partners for the attention of your request.
We will also share your information sub-processors in order to provide you with the services according to this Privacy Policy.
In addition, we will share and disclose your personal information to the hotel in which you make a reservation for stay in order to process your booking.
Cross-country data transmission
Whereas MHI is a global hotel group, for the purposes set forth in this Privacy Policy and to achieve MHI's purpose of providing you with premium and quality services worldwide, with your sole consent (if required by applicable law), your personal information will be transmitted to MHI located oversea at Calle Gremio Toneleros, number 24, Palma de Mallorca, Spain, and may be transmitted to other MHI affiliated entities or hotel entities in which you make a reservation for stay located at other countries or regions, and such affiliated entities and/or hotel entities will process your personal information for the purposes and in the manner described in this Privacy Policy. MHI will take appropriate measures to ensure that the cross-border transfer of data and the processing of your personal information by MHI's overseas affiliated entities comply with the requirements of applicable law. Such mechanisms are designed to ensure adequate protection of your personal information in accordance with applicable law. If you wish to exercise your rights with respect to personal information you may contact MHI at privacy@melia.com.
How we store and protect your personal information
We will store your personal information for as long as necessary to achieve the purposes set forth in this Privacy Policy, for the duration of your use of our services, and otherwise as required by applicable law. We will take reasonable security measures to protect your personal information in accordance with industry standards, and are committed to using various technologies and measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, use, modification, disclosure and damage of such information, such as the use of encryption technology to protect your personal information. We will handle personal information security incidents in accordance with applicable laws and regulations, and provide personal information protection training to relevant personnel to enhance their awareness of the importance of personal information and responsibilities related to personal information protection.
SDKS and other similar software technologies provided by unaffiliated entities
According to PRC laws, MHI must disclose the SDK for your acknowledgement. In the course of providing products or services, we may deploy plug-ins that are not associated with entities, such as software development kit SDK, statistical analysis tools, etc., which may collect your personal information. In order to facilitate your understanding of the SDKS of the non-associated entities we use, you can refer to the following SDK list to learn more about our integrated SDK information.
If you use these features and plug-ins provided by unaffiliated entities, the privacy policies of those entities may also apply to you. Some of these entities may collect data from you for their use and processing, and may seek your consent before doing so. In any case, we recommend that you read the privacy policies of these unaffiliated entities before using their features and plug-ins to understand how they collect and process your data.
