Mobile device permission
If you choose to use the feature to search for hotels near your location, we will require you to provide authorization to access your location information in order to run this feature.
Personalized commercial communications
In order to help you better obtain the information you are interested in, we may collect your personal information to provide you with personalized commercial communications.
If a customer wishes to stop receiving MHI's commercial or promotional messages, he/she may request cancellation by (i) sending an email to the following address: privacy@melia.com indicating in the email that he/she does not wish to receive such commercial and promotional information or (ii) using the withdrawal option provided in each of the commercial communications sent.
Your rights
In addition to the rights mentioned in this Privacy Policy, you also enjoy the following rights as permitted by the data protection laws of the People's Republic of China:
Access your personal information and obtain a copy of the information
You have the right to access personal information held by us about you or to obtain copies of such information.
Transfer your personal information
You have the right to request that your personal information be transmitted to another data controller as permitted by applicable law.
Close your account
You also have the right to contact china.policy@melia.com and request that we close your MeliáRewards loyalty program account.
The right to request deletion and correction of information
You may ask us to correct any incorrect information about you (see the "Exercise of Rights" section for details). We are happy to correct such information, but we need to verify its accuracy first.
If you believe that it is no longer necessary for us to use your information for the purpose for which it was collected, you may request that we delete your information. In addition, you may request us to delete your information if you have revoked your consent to our use of your information (if we originally asked you to consent to our use of your information), or have exercised your right against further lawful use of your information, or if we have used your information unlawfully, or if we are bound by legal obligations to delete your personal information.
In individual cases, we may not be able to meet your requirements. Examples of such situations include when we need to continue to use your information to fulfill our legal obligations, or when we need to use your information to establish a legitimate claim, enforce a legal right, or defend a legal claim.
The right to revoke consent to permission to use mobile devices
You can revoke authorization or consent to use of the mobile device in the Settings options for the device.
To exercise any of the above rights, you can also contact us by sending an email to China.Policy@melia.com.
We aim to respond to all valid requests for exercising the above rights within 15 working days after verifying your identity. In order to be able to respond more quickly, we may ask you to provide more detailed information related to your inquiry.
In individual cases, we may not be able to comply with your request, for example, your request may affect our duty of confidentiality to others, or we may be legally entitled to handle your request differently.
Privacy policy update
MHI reserves the right to update or modify this policy from time to time. If our privacy policy changes, we will post the latest version of the privacy policy here. If we make a material change to our privacy policy, we may also notify you of the change through various channels, for example, by posting a notice on our website or by posting a separate notice to you.
How to contact us
